Description: Body and rim sherd of North Ionian pottery rosette bowl; pale brown clay with some silver mica; interior: glazed band at top; reserved below with dilute line; exterior: dot-rosette; inscribed on exterior
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 317)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 670, no. 278)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.846)
